quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  28,51,"And We caused the Word to reach them, per chance (or possibly) they may be mindful"
  28,52,"Those to whom We gave the Book before it (the Quran), they believe therein"
  28,53,"And when it is recited to them they say, \"We believe in it. It is the Truth from Our Lord. Verily, we were, even before it came, of those who Surrender (or were Muslim)"
  28,54,"These shall be given their reward twice over, because they were steadfast, and repelled evil with good, and spend of what We have bestowed upon them"
  28,55,"And when they hear vain talk, they turn away from it and say, \"We have our works, and you have your works. Peace be upon you! We do not seek the ignorant"
  28,56,"Verily, you can not guide whom you do like, but Allah guides whom He wills; for He knows best who are to be guided"
  28,57,"And they say, \"If we follow the Guidance we shall be snatched away from the land.\" Have We not established for them a safe sanctuary, to which are imported the fruits of all things as a provision from Us? But most of them know not"
  28,58,"How many a community have We destroyed that exulted in its means of subsistence? Yonder are their dwellings which have not been inhabited after them, except for a while. And We, even We, are the inheritors"
  28,59,But your Lord would never destroy a community until He has sent to its centre a messenger to recite to them Our signs; nor would We destroy populations unless their people practiced iniquity
  28,60,"Whatever thing you may be given, it is a provision for the life of this world and the adornment thereof; but that which Allah has is better and more enduring. Have you then no sense"
  28,61,"Is He to whom We have promised a goodly promise, which he shall meet with, like him to whom We have given the enjoyment in the life of this world, and who on the Day of Resurrection shall be of the arraigned (brought up to deserve punishment)"
  28,62,"And on the Day when He will call them and say, \"Where are My partners which you imagined"
  28,63,"And those concerning whom the Word will have come true shall say, \"Our Lord! These are those whom we have seduced away; we seduced them as we were seduced ourselves: but we declare our innocence before Thee - they did not worship us"
  28,64,"And it will be said, \"Call upon your pretend partners; and they will call upon them, but they will not answer them, and they shall see the Doom. Ah, would that they had been guided right"
  28,65,"And on the Day when He shall call unto them and say, \"What was it you answered the messengers"
  28,66,"And history shall be obscure to them on that day, nor shall they ask each other"
  28,67,"But, as for him who repents and believes and does right, it may be that he will be among the successful"
  28,68,For your Lord brings to pass what He pleases and chooses; they have never the choice! Glorified be Allah and exalted above all they associate with Him
  28,69,Your Lord knows what they conceal in their breasts and what they manifest
  28,70,"He is Allah; there is no God but He; to Him belongs all praise, in the first place (or state) and the last; and His is the command; and unto Him shall you return"
  28,71,"Have you considered, if Allah were to make for you the night endless until the Day of Resurrection, who is the god, but Allah, to bring you light? Will you not then hear"
  28,72,"Say, \"Have you considered, if Allah were to make for you the day endless until the Day of Judgment, who is the god, except Allah, to bring you the night to rest therein? Can you not then see"
  28,73,"But of His mercy He has made for you the night and the day, that you may rest therein, and crave of His grace, per chance (or possibly) you may give thanks"
  28,74,"And the day when He shall call them and say, \"Where are my partners whom you did pretend were such"
  28,75,"And We will pluck from every nation a witness; and We will say, \"Bring your proof and know that the truth belongs to Allah\". And that which they had devised shall stray away from them"